WEBVTT

00:11.680 --> 00:13.640
[BEEPING]

00:16.476 --> 00:18.561
We'll be right there, commissioner.

00:50.218 --> 00:52.012
ROBIN: I agree with the commissioner,
Batman.

00:52.220 --> 00:54.639
This clue looks like it points
to the Gotham River.

00:54.848 --> 00:57.392
There's always more to a clue
than what meets the eye.

00:57.642 --> 00:59.519
Crazy Quilt's paintings
are no exception.

00:59.728 --> 01:01.855
He's referring to waves of light,
not water.

01:02.063 --> 01:05.984
Red, blue and green are the basic colors
by which the human eye perceives light.

01:11.197 --> 01:14.200
Here's where we'll find
that flamboyant fiend.

01:14.409 --> 01:18.329
Quilt is after the extremely dangerous
stimulated emission light amplifier.

01:30.175 --> 01:31.801
Gosh, Batman, you're right again.

01:32.010 --> 01:34.804
No time to rest on our laurels, Robin.
Stay alert.

01:37.515 --> 01:40.310
Hold it right there, Quilt.
We cracked your color clues.

01:40.518 --> 01:42.562
And now you're painted into a corner.

01:42.771 --> 01:44.564
The Dynamic Duo.

01:44.773 --> 01:48.026
Allow me to introduce my comrades,
the Color Guard.

01:48.234 --> 01:50.528
They'll make abstracts of both of you.

01:51.905 --> 01:53.573
[GRUNTING]

02:11.674 --> 02:14.469
Ha. The Caped Crusaders win again.

02:14.677 --> 02:16.137
[LIGHT AMPLIFIER POWERING UP]

02:18.723 --> 02:23.061
I will carve the cityscape into
a masterpiece to rival Mount Rushmore.

02:23.269 --> 02:26.689
That's a pretty ambitious plan
for a guy who can barely dress himself.

02:26.940 --> 02:28.191
No taunting, Robin.

02:28.399 --> 02:29.359
[GASPS]

02:29.609 --> 02:31.694
Insolent whelp.

02:36.366 --> 02:41.454
Cowards.
Step forth and submit to my genius.

02:51.506 --> 02:53.758
Holy delusions of grandeur, Batman.

02:53.967 --> 02:56.469
I think Quilt is a few colors short
of a rainbow.

02:56.719 --> 03:00.098
He needs to be taught
to stay between the lines.

03:00.473 --> 03:04.519
Sacrifice yourself
and go from mere men...

03:04.769 --> 03:07.021
...to masterpieces.

03:22.162 --> 03:23.454
[SCREAMS]

03:29.794 --> 03:32.213
I guess Crazy Quilt
finally saw the light, Batman.

03:32.422 --> 03:33.423
Yes, Robin.

03:33.631 --> 03:37.635
He's learned the hard way
that justice is blind.

04:21.095 --> 04:22.764
COP:
Come out with your hands up.

04:32.148 --> 04:34.234
[GROANING]

04:39.405 --> 04:41.783
COP:
That's not gonna work on him.

04:41.991 --> 04:46.287
Omega alert. Officer in need of backup.
The big backup.

05:09.060 --> 05:11.562
Walking out the front door
with a 2-ton safe?

05:11.771 --> 05:14.315
You're about as subtle
as you are smart, Grundy.

05:25.868 --> 05:27.287
Mind if I borrow that?

05:29.998 --> 05:32.041
[GRUNTING]

05:32.292 --> 05:36.421
I may be small, but around here,
I'm the big man in charge.

05:36.629 --> 05:39.090
No boss. No lectures.

05:43.845 --> 05:44.846
And the best part...

05:52.020 --> 05:54.939
...I get to have all the fun to myself.

06:04.407 --> 06:06.659
He's all yours, officer.

06:07.660 --> 06:08.661
Thank you, Robin.

06:08.870 --> 06:12.999
The citizens of Bludhaven
can sleep safer knowing you're on patrol.

06:15.084 --> 06:16.419
Bludhaven may look filthy...

06:16.627 --> 06:20.423
...but at least I've cleaned
the criminal scum off the streets.

06:23.426 --> 06:26.846
Even though some people thought
I couldn't make it on my own.

06:33.186 --> 06:35.521
- Strange. It looks like--
BATMAN: Morse code.

06:35.730 --> 06:38.483
It spells out an address
on the corner of Haney and Aparo.

06:38.691 --> 06:41.527
What are you doing here?
Shouldn't you be in a whale's belly...

06:41.736 --> 06:44.364
-...with Aquaman or something?
- Crazy Quilt escaped.

06:44.614 --> 06:46.032
From Arkham, I know.

06:46.282 --> 06:48.659
Good. Then you know
it's you he's after.

06:48.868 --> 06:54.374
Yeah. I've got it under control.
See you at the next Bat-family reunion.

06:59.253 --> 07:02.423
You have no idea
how deranged Quilt's become.

07:02.673 --> 07:05.468
You always knew more than I did
about criminals, right?

07:05.718 --> 07:08.513
Look, I know you left Gotham
so you could be your own man...

07:08.721 --> 07:12.058
...but I'm only here to help.
It'll be just like old times.

07:12.934 --> 07:16.521
- Fine. But just remember--
- Follow my lead.

07:16.771 --> 07:19.190
--You're in my city now.

07:27.573 --> 07:29.534
It could be a trap.
Stay behind me, Robin.

07:29.742 --> 07:33.788
If you're worried about my well-being,
maybe I'd be safer back in the cave...

07:34.038 --> 07:39.001
...rotating the tires on the Batmobile.
You know, like old times.

07:39.752 --> 07:43.506
Speedy had to sharpen arrows.
Aqualad had to scrape barnacles.

07:43.714 --> 07:46.592
Everyone earns their stripes.

07:55.476 --> 07:57.395
Stay alert.

08:03.317 --> 08:04.444
Red fish?

08:04.694 --> 08:07.113
- A red herring, to be precise, Robin.
- That means...

08:07.363 --> 08:10.241
-...he's throwing us off the trail.
- It means more than that.

08:10.450 --> 08:12.702
The painter Henri Matisse
abandoned his brush...

08:12.910 --> 08:15.913
...in favor of paper cutouts
for the same reason Quilt has.

08:16.122 --> 08:17.665
He's blind.

08:17.874 --> 08:20.334
QUILT [OVER LOUDSPEAKER]:
Brilliant as always, Batman.

08:20.543 --> 08:25.548
Unlike Matisse, however,
I was blinded by a prepubescent brat.

08:25.756 --> 08:28.551
Quilt, you're a lousy artist
and a lousier villain.

08:28.801 --> 08:32.763
If you've got the guts to show yourself,
I'll gladly take you on alone.

08:32.972 --> 08:35.808
QUILT:
Then come and get me, little birdie.

08:36.517 --> 08:38.311
Wait, Robin, it's a trick.

08:38.519 --> 08:40.813
I can handle
whatever this Z-lister's got.

08:43.649 --> 08:44.984
[GRUNTS]

08:49.030 --> 08:50.531
[GRUNTING]

09:06.339 --> 09:08.007
Warned you.

09:11.177 --> 09:12.887
[QUILT LAUGHING]

09:13.095 --> 09:15.264
A good likeness, don't you think?

09:15.473 --> 09:19.227
Without sight, I'm forced to be
a little more creative with my art.

09:19.435 --> 09:22.980
Coward. Open the door and face me.

09:23.814 --> 09:26.692
I wasn't up all night
cutting out paper fish...

09:26.901 --> 09:30.363
...just to have a boxing match
with you, boy.

09:30.613 --> 09:34.200
I have something much bigger in mind.

09:34.575 --> 09:38.538
In the meantime, my kaleidoscope
will generate enough centripetal force...

09:38.746 --> 09:42.083
...to flatten you
into two-dimensional masterpieces...

09:42.291 --> 09:46.128
...that will hang
in my private collection.

09:58.391 --> 10:00.768
The spinning force
combined with physical pressure...

10:00.977 --> 10:03.271
...could be enough to puncture the wall
with the Batarang.

10:03.479 --> 10:06.566
We'll be crushed by then.
The projector for the light patterns...

10:06.774 --> 10:09.360
...should be plugged into
the same power source as the machine.

10:09.569 --> 10:11.612
[GRUNTING]

10:14.407 --> 10:17.702
If I can just hit it with the Batlaser...

10:27.461 --> 10:28.504
More often than not...

10:28.713 --> 10:32.008
...escaping a deathtrap
is about quick thinking, not brute force.

10:32.508 --> 10:34.427
Yeah, but my way worked too.

10:35.553 --> 10:37.388
Quilt said he's after something bigger.

10:37.597 --> 10:40.975
We need to find out what, fast.
Let's move.

10:44.061 --> 10:48.482
ROBIN:
Oh, man. He trashed my bike.

10:50.234 --> 10:51.485
Not to worry, Robin.

10:57.408 --> 11:00.411
Please, not the sidecar.

11:05.499 --> 11:08.336
- I thought you liked the sidecar.
- Yeah, when I was 8.

11:08.794 --> 11:12.006
Look, I can handle this alone.
It's me he wants.

11:15.217 --> 11:17.511
That's precisely why
you won't handle it alone.

11:17.720 --> 11:19.972
Quilt is a madman
and more dangerous than ever.

11:20.181 --> 11:22.850
But he still can't resist leaving clues
to his crimes.

11:23.059 --> 11:25.936
Have there been any art thefts
in Bludhaven since he escaped?

11:26.145 --> 11:30.358
Van Gogh's Starry Night was on loan to
the museum. It went missing yesterday.

11:30.608 --> 11:33.027
It must mean
Quilt is heading to S.T.A.R. Labs.

11:34.445 --> 11:36.030
I've got it. Starry Night.

11:36.280 --> 11:38.574
It must mean
Quilt is heading to S.T.A.R. Labs.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.761
Boy, am I glad to see you, Batman.

11:58.969 --> 12:01.722
They're after
the stimulated emission light amplifier.

12:01.931 --> 12:04.767
That's what Quilt was after
when we put him away years ago.

12:12.858 --> 12:14.568
ROBIN:
Arts and crafts are over, Quilt.

12:20.741 --> 12:22.827
The Boy Blunder.

12:23.035 --> 12:25.621
Alas, I was hoping
you would be flat enough...

12:25.830 --> 12:28.332
...to fold into a little paper hat
by now.

12:28.582 --> 12:34.922
Instead, I'll make you the centerpiece
of a much more ambitious installation.

12:36.173 --> 12:37.842
[GRUNTING]

12:50.020 --> 12:52.106
Let the scientist go.

12:52.314 --> 12:55.693
QUILT:
Batman, always ordering people around.

12:57.445 --> 12:58.863
[LAUGHS]

12:59.363 --> 13:01.699
Well, now you can answer to me.

13:11.792 --> 13:14.378
- Quilt's all mine.
BATMAN: No.

13:14.628 --> 13:17.548
You go after Red.
He's probably prepping their getaway.

13:17.757 --> 13:19.800
You always make me
go after the henchmen.

13:20.009 --> 13:23.179
Because you're good at it. Now, go.

13:40.196 --> 13:43.741
"You're good at it."
Quilt is my villain, and this is my city.

13:44.200 --> 13:45.409
All I want is a little...

13:47.244 --> 13:49.079
...respect?

13:52.750 --> 13:54.210
This is just redundant.

13:55.461 --> 13:56.879
[GRUNTING]

14:01.634 --> 14:05.137
You can't even see well enough to use
that thing. What's your game, Quilt?

14:05.346 --> 14:08.390
True, you're nothing
but a big blue blob...

14:08.599 --> 14:11.727
...but when I have this device
wired into my optic nerves...

14:11.936 --> 14:17.691
...I'll be able to carve a building
into a work of art just by looking at it.

14:24.740 --> 14:27.743
You're a sick, lost soul, Quilt.
Give yourself up.

14:27.993 --> 14:31.288
No. It's you who's lost.

14:33.040 --> 14:34.291
[GRUNTS]

14:56.063 --> 14:59.275
You always wanted to escape
the shadow of the Bat, Robin.

14:59.483 --> 15:01.944
Here's your chance.

15:02.152 --> 15:05.990
You're gonna wish you stayed in Arkham
with your coloring books.

15:09.368 --> 15:11.662
I'm going to weave you both
into carpets...

15:11.871 --> 15:16.000
...and spend the rest of my life
walking all over you.

15:26.510 --> 15:29.471
Call me a coward now, you little runt.

15:29.680 --> 15:31.265
Quilt, we gotta go.

15:33.309 --> 15:36.687
Who's laughing now, little birdie?

15:36.896 --> 15:39.148
Who's laughing now?

15:39.356 --> 15:41.400
[LAUGHING]

15:41.901 --> 15:43.152
Quilt, the cops.

15:43.360 --> 15:44.653
[SIREN WAILING]

15:44.862 --> 15:45.946
Very well.

15:56.457 --> 15:58.500
[ROBIN GRUNTING]

16:13.140 --> 16:15.768
For years, I sat in that cell...

16:16.018 --> 16:19.813
...listening to Robin's exploits
on the radio...

16:20.022 --> 16:25.653
...dreaming of his annihilation,
destroying him over and over.

16:25.861 --> 16:28.155
With the modifications to my helmet...

16:28.364 --> 16:33.452
...I will pull apart this whole city
in his name, telling the citizens:

16:33.661 --> 16:37.665
"This is all Robin's fault."

16:45.381 --> 16:47.424
[ROBIN GRUNTING]

17:04.984 --> 17:08.862
ROBIN: Quilt always leaves a clue.
This time, he left one by accident.

17:09.530 --> 17:11.782
If I were going to turn Batman
into a carpet...

17:11.991 --> 17:14.118
...there's only one place to do it.

17:30.217 --> 17:33.095
ROBIN:
Quilt gave you lookout duty, huh?

17:34.096 --> 17:35.973
Yeah, I used to get lookout duty too.

17:40.602 --> 17:44.398
And after all these years,
Batman still treats me like I'm a little kid.

17:45.107 --> 17:47.151
[GRUNTING]

17:52.698 --> 17:54.658
Thanks for listening.

18:10.424 --> 18:12.509
[GRUNTING]

18:22.352 --> 18:25.022
- Now, that's just creepy.
BATMAN: Good job, Robin.

18:25.230 --> 18:28.067
You have to get me out of here quickly,
so listen carefully.

18:28.275 --> 18:29.443
No, you listen.

18:29.651 --> 18:31.904
I've got some things
I wanna get off my chest.

18:32.112 --> 18:34.823
First off, I'm not a child anymore.

18:35.032 --> 18:38.911
So I don't need you checking up on me
and always looking over my shoulder.

18:39.119 --> 18:41.455
Sure, you taught me a lot
when I was a kid.

18:41.663 --> 18:44.583
But I'm an adult now,
and I've got my own city to look after.

18:44.792 --> 18:47.044
I don't need help.
I don't chase henchmen.

18:47.294 --> 18:50.964
I don't get the costumes dry-cleaned.
And I don't ride in sidecars.

18:51.215 --> 18:54.301
Admit it, Batman,
I'm just as good as you.

18:54.593 --> 18:56.053
Huh?

18:58.639 --> 19:00.974
Thanks for taking out the henchmen.

19:02.017 --> 19:05.104
Yeah. Apparently, that's my specialty.

19:05.562 --> 19:07.189
[LIGHT AMPLIFIER POWERING UP]

19:25.415 --> 19:30.420
It seems I get the pleasure
of destroying you twice in one day.

19:30.671 --> 19:32.464
Fine, I'll sit for a portrait...

19:32.673 --> 19:34.842
...but make sure you get my good side,
okay?

19:35.050 --> 19:38.720
I made a few modifications.

19:38.929 --> 19:42.015
Now I can wipe you out
with a mere thought.

19:47.771 --> 19:51.733
The world is my canvas,
and you'll be my paint.

20:04.121 --> 20:06.165
[LAUGHING]

20:21.263 --> 20:23.348
He's got us cornered.

20:24.725 --> 20:27.853
- So, what's the plan?
- Your villain, your call.

20:31.398 --> 20:33.358
I'm on it.

20:36.862 --> 20:40.032
QUILT: I'll bring this entire city clown
on top of us...

20:40.240 --> 20:42.534
...if that's what it takes, boy.

20:53.879 --> 20:55.881
[LAUGHING]

21:02.471 --> 21:06.892
Batman was always a father to me.
That doesn't mean I forgot my roots.

21:07.142 --> 21:09.186
[GROANS]

21:14.316 --> 21:15.525
[GRUNTS]

21:23.742 --> 21:27.996
Once a Flying Grayson,
always a Flying Grayson.

21:33.627 --> 21:35.420
[GROANING]

21:38.632 --> 21:40.550
- Well done, old chum.
ROBIN: Thanks.

21:40.759 --> 21:43.637
I'm glad you finally have faith
I can do things on my own.

21:43.845 --> 21:45.847
I've always had faith in you, Robin.

21:46.056 --> 21:49.726
That's why I trusted you
to work the streets of Bludhaven solo.

21:51.270 --> 21:53.772
Well, I learned from the best.

21:53.981 --> 21:55.607
[BEEPER RINGING]

21:56.817 --> 21:58.402
The commissioner just called.

21:58.610 --> 22:01.405
Killer Moth hijacked
the Gotham Bank money train.

22:01.613 --> 22:06.410
- If you're up for it.
- Gosh, I'd-- I mean, sure, I'm up for it.

22:06.660 --> 22:08.537
Then let's roll.
